originalText.text:
Supreme Deli is like the proverbial new kid, I tried them once a like a little over a year ago and to put it nicely I wasn’t happy with the food or the service. Now I’m rather forgiving and recognize sometimes you catch a business on a off day. Which I’m pretty sure that was the case.
Since I now work in the area I felt it was time to give them another go. First with something simple Coffee. They’re coffee is surprisingly good. I recently tried their steak quesadilla which was very good and their cheeseburger deluxe. Now the   Cheeseburger was good but they get brownie points for serving crinkle cut French fries. So the food is vastly better than my first experience.
Service the staff are all amenable and engaging but to me the star of their staff is the young lady at the register she’s always pleasant , friendly and professional.

originalText.text:
Clean, nice, fast service

Unfortunately, I had the worst Chicken Parm Panini I've ever had from any NYC deli. No discernable protein and it just tasted like cheap, fake plastic cheese with no trace of tomato sauce.

originalText.text:
Disclaimer: I was a tourist when I went here

I came in every morning for five days. The staff was really friendly, the coffee wasn't bad, and the food was great. I ate tons while I was in NYC, but would go to bed looking forward to getting up and picking a new item off this deli's menu.

originalText.text: EVERY single time I go to this deli they have gotten my order wrong. The woman who works the register is super nice and I like talking to her but even this morning I ordered Tuna with cheddar and lettuce on a whole wheat wrap and they forgot both the cheddar and the lettuce. The only two things I asked for on it. Another time they ASKED me if I wanted avocado on my egg white wrap, I said no, and they gave it to me anyway.

originalText.text: The man working last night was so incredibly kind! I tried to buy a phone charger as my phone was dead, and instead he charged my phone behind the counter and let me wait inside until I had enough battery to safely call a ride home. Really good humans work here, care about the people that walk into the deli. Thank you Sandeep!
